HEADWORD: Cranioclasm
<hw>Cra"ni*o*clasm</hw> <pr>(kr?"n?-?-kl?z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Cranium</ets> + Gr. <?/<?/<?/ to break.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The crushing of a child's head, as with the
cranioclast or craniotomy forceps in cases of very difficult
delivery.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
